$ torchrun --nproc_per_node=2 code/expert_parallel_demo.py
=================================================================
Expert Parallelism Demo
=================================================================

World size: 2 GPUs = 2 experts

Configuration:
  Tokens per GPU: 16
  Hidden dim: 256
  Expert dim: 512
  Top-k routing: 2

-----------------------------------------------------------------
Running Expert-Parallel Forward Pass
-----------------------------------------------------------------

  Router assigned tokens to experts:
    Expert 0: 12 token-expert pairs
    Expert 1: 4 token-expert pairs

  Token dispatch (top-1 only for demo):
    GPU 0 sends: [12, 4]
    GPU 0 receives: [12, 6]

  After all-to-all dispatch:
    GPU 0 now has 18 tokens to process with Expert 0

-----------------------------------------------------------------
Summary
-----------------------------------------------------------------
  Input shape per GPU: (16, 256)
  Output shape per GPU: (16, 256)

  Key steps:
    1. Router computes expert assignments for each token
    2. All-to-all dispatches tokens to their assigned experts
    3. Each GPU processes tokens with its local expert
    4. All-to-all returns results to original GPUs
    5. Results weighted by router scores
=================================================================

